<!-- $title Make My Bourbon Neat -->
<!-- $SEO-title Make my Bourbon Neat - the Bourbon and Neat mixin libraries -->
<!-- $description Bourbon, a lightweight library of sass mixins that help designers create quick, quality code. Neat built on top of Bourbon is a lightweight grid framework. -->
<!-- $keyword Bourbon, Neat, Scss, Css -->
<!-- $url bourbon-neat.html -->
<!-- $post-image img/bourbon-mixins-image.jpg -->

<!-- @import ../includes/_header -->

<article class="post">
 
 <!-- @import includes/_parallax -->
  
  <div class="post-content inner bourbon">

<blockquote><p><strong>Bourbon</strong>, a lightweight library of sass mixins from <a href="https://thoughtbot.com/">thoughtbot</a>, helps designers create quick, quality code. Being a small library it doesn't take long to pick-up. <strong>Neat</strong> is built on top of Bourbon, and is a lightweight grid framework for Sass. And like Bourbon, being lightweight it's easy to pick-up.  </p></blockquote>

<h2>Bourbon</h2>

<p>The Bourbon mixin library had quite a change for version 5, becoming a lot lighter. Now up-to version 6, <em>not much different from 5</em>, the mixins below are what's available at present (<em>keep checking the Bourbon website for mixin information</em>). For more information about the <em>Bourbon mixin library</em> see <a href="https://github.com/thoughtbot/bourbon">Bourbon</a> on the Github website and <a href="http://bourbon.io/docs/">Bourbon Docs</a> on the Bourbon website.</p>
    
  <hr>
