<h2 id="font-stacks">Font Stacks</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
font-family: $font-stack-helvetica;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Helvetica Neue", "Helvetica", "Arial", sans-serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-lucida-grande;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Lucida Grande", "Lucida Sans Unicode", "Geneva", "Verdana", sans-serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-verdana;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Verdana", "Geneva", sans-serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-system;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Avenir Next", "Avenir", "Segoe UI", "Lucida Grande", "Helvetica Neue", "Helvetica", "Fira Sans", "Roboto", "Noto", "Droid Sans", "Cantarell", "Oxygen", "Ubuntu", "Franklin Gothic Medium", "Century Gothic", "Liberation Sans", sans-serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-garamond;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Garamond", "Baskerville", "Baskerville Old Face", "Hoefler Text", "Times New Roman", serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-georgia;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Georgia", "Times", "Times New Roman", serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-hoefler-text;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Hoefler Text", "Baskerville Old Face", "Garamond", "Times New Roman", serif;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-consolas;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Consolas", "monaco", monospace;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-courier-new;
}
// CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Courier New", "Courier", "Lucida Sans Typewriter", "Lucida Typewriter", monospace;
}
_________
.element {
font-family: $font-stack-monaco;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-family: "Monaco", "Consolas", "Lucida Console", monospace;
}</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2 id="hide-text">Hide Text</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
@include hide-text;
}
//CSS Output
.element {
overflow: hidden;
text-indent: 101%;
white-space: nowrap;
}</code></pre></p>
<hr>
<h2 id="hide-visually">Hide Visually</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">button.below {
@include size(180px, 40px);
span {
@include hide-visually;
}
&:hover span {
@include hide-visually("unhide");
}
}
</code></pre>
<p>The button below hides the text via a <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> using the style above, hover to view the text</p>
<button class="below"><span>This title is hidden</span></button>
<hr>
<h2 id="margin">Margin</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
@include margin(20px 3em 10vh null);
}
//CSS Output
.element {
margin-top: 20px;
margin-right: 3em;
margin-bottom: 10vh;
}
</code></pre>
        
<div class="eight">
<p>This text is using the mixin above to set this paragraph margins in this box</p>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id="scale">Modular Scale</h2>
<p>Increments up or down a defined scale and returns an adjusted value. This helps establish consistent measurements throughout your project.<br>
For more information about Modular Scales start <a href="http://bourbon.io/docs/#modular-scale">here</a></p>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">//Globally change the base ratio
$bourbon: (
"modular-scale-ratio": 1.2,
);
.element {
font-size: modular-scale(3);
}
//CSS Output
.element {
font-size: 1.728em;
}
</code></pre>
            
<div class="nine">
<p>This text is using the style above to set the font size</p>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id="wrap">Overflow Wrap</h2>
<p>Outputs the <em>overflow-wrap</em> property and its legacy name <em>word-wrap</em> to support browsers that do not yet use <em>overflow-wrap</em></p>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">Accepted CSS values are normal, break-word, inherit, initial or unset.
@example scss
.wrapper {
@include overflow-wrap;
}
//CSS Output
.wrapper {
word-wrap: break-word;
overflow-wrap: break-word;
}
</code></pre>
            
<div class="ten">
<p>Thisisaveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryveryverylongword</p>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id="padding">Padding</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
@include padding(50px 5% 10vh null);
}
//CSS Output
.element {
padding-top: 50px;
padding-right: 5%;
padding-bottom: 10vh;
}
</code></pre>
            
<div class="eleven">
<p>This text is using the mixin above to set this paragraph padding in this box</p>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id="position">Position</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
@include position(absolute, 10px null null 10px);
}
//CSS Output
.element {
position: absolute;
top: 10px;
left: 10px;
}
</code></pre>
            
<div class="twelve">
<div></div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id="prefixer">Prefixer</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
@include prefixer(appearance, none, ("webkit", "moz"));
}
//CSS Output
.element {
-webkit-appearance: none;
-moz-appearance: none;
appearance: none;
}</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2 id="shade">Shade</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
background-color: shade(#ffbb52, 60%);
}
//CSS Output
.element {
background-color: #664a20;
}</code></pre>
            
<div class="thirteen"></div>
<hr>
<h2 id="size">Size</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.first-element {
@include size(5em);
}
//CSS Output
.first-element {
width: 5em;
height: 5em;
}
.second-element {
@include size(1em, 2em);
}
//CSS Output
.second-element {
width: 1em;
height: 2em;
}</code></pre>
            
<div class="fourteen">
<div></div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id="strip">Strip Unit</h2>
<p>Strips the unit from a number</p>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">$dimension: strip-unit(10em);
//Output
$dimension: 10;</code></pre>
<hr>
