<hr>
<h2 id="tint">Tint</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
background-color: tint(#6ecaa6, 40%);
}
//CSS Output
.element {
background-color: #a8dfc9;
}</code></pre>
            
<div class="fifteen"></div>
<hr>
<h2 id="triangle">Triangle</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
&::before {
@include triangle("up", 2rem, 1rem, #b25c9c);//direction, width, height, color of triangle
content: "";
}
}
                        
//CSS Output
.element::before {
border-style: solid;
height: 0;
width: 0;
border-color: transparent transparent #b25c9c;
border-width: 0 1rem 1rem;//width or height /2 depends on direction - in this case arrow "up" width is halved
content: "";
}
//style used for element below
.element {
border: $border;
@include size(4rem);//size of box
position: relative;
&::before {
@include triangle("up", 2rem, 2rem, #b25c9c);//width /2 on output
position: absolute;
content: "";
top:-2rem;//position triangle on box
left:1rem;//position triangle on box
}
}</code></pre>
            
<div class="sixteen"></div>
<hr>
            
<h2 id="value">Value Prefixer</h2>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.element {
@include value-prefixer(cursor, grab, ("webkit", "moz"));
}
//CSS Output
.element {
cursor: -webkit-grab;
cursor: -moz-grab;
cursor: grab;
}</code></pre>

<hr>

<!-- -------------------------------------------------->

<h2 id="grids">Neat Grids</h2>

<p>Bourbon Neat, <em>a lightweight grid framework for Sass</em>, totally changed in version 2, now up-to version 6, it's easy to pick-up <strong>but unfortunately it's no longer maintained</strong>. Phone1st uses CodeKit's copy of the Neat library and shown here are some basic grid settings, but with <em>Flexbox</em> and <em>CSS Grids</em> are the grid framework's day's numbered?</p>
<p>Don't forget to check the <a href="https://neat.bourbon.io/">Bourbon Neat</a> website for more information.</p>

<h3>Something to watch</h3>

<p>Take a look at <em>Page with one sidebar</em> and <em>Page with two sidebars</em>. Both have a <em>background color, red</em>. Notice the <em>Page with one sidebar</em> has margins left and right set to whatever the <em>gutter</em> is set to. This seems to be default which seems strange. The <em>Page with two sidebars</em> has no margins left or right but has an extra <em>div</em> element set to <em>collapse</em> the grid, which works a treat. Also see the <a href="http://neat.bourbon.io">Bourbon Neat</a> website for more examples and info.</p>
<hr>
<h5>Grid Variables</h5>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">@import "neat";

//over-riding the default neat gutter setting
$neat-grid: (
  columns: 12,
  gutter: 10px,
);
//new grid settings
$small-grid: (
  columns: 4,
  gutter: 10px,
  media: 600px,
);
$medium-grid: (
  columns: 8,
  gutter: 20px,
  media: 740px,
);
$large-grid: (
  columns: 8,
  gutter: 20px,
  media: 900px,
);
$box-color: #486cb8;
$height: 120px;</code></pre>
<hr>
  
  <div class="grid-box">
    <h5>Page with one sidebar</h5>
  <div class="one-sidebar">
  <div class="one-sidebar-a"></div>
  <div class="one-sidebar-b"></div>
  </div><!-- one-sidebar -->
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.one-sidebar {
 @include grid-container;
 background: $error-color;//red
}
.one-sidebar-a {
 @include grid-column(9);
 background: $box-color;
 height: $height;
}
.one-sidebar-b {
 @include grid-column(3);
 background: $box-color;
 height: $height;
}</code></pre>
<hr>
    <h5>Page with two sidebars</h5>
  <div class="two-sidebar">
  <div class="two-sidebar-inner">
  <div class="two-sidebar-a"></div>
  <div class="two-sidebar-b"></div>
  <div class="two-sidebar-c"></div>
  </div><!-- two-sidebar-inner -->
  </div><!-- two-sidebar -->

<pre><code class="lang-scss">.two-sidebar {
 @include grid-container;
 background: $error-color;
 overflow-x: hidden;
}
.two-sidebar-inner {
 @include grid-collapse();
}
.two-sidebar-a {
 @include grid-column(3);
 background: $box-color;
 height: $height;
}
.two-sidebar-b {
 @include grid-column(6);
 background: $box-color;
 height: $height;
}
.two-sidebar-c {
 @include grid-column(3);
 background: $box-color;
 height: $height;
}</code></pre>
<hr>
    <h5>Nested columns</h5>
  <div class="nested-columns">
  <div class="nested-columns-a"></div>
  <div class="nested-columns-b">
  <div class="nested-wrap">
  <div class="nested-columns-b-one"></div>
  <div class="nested-columns-b-one"></div>
  <div class="nested-columns-b-one"></div>
  <div class="nested-columns-b-one"></div>
  <div class="nested-columns-b-one"></div>
  <div class="nested-columns-b-one"></div>
  </div><!-- nested-wrap -->
  </div><!-- nested-columns-b -->
  </div><!-- nested-columns -->
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.nested-columns {
 @include grid-container;
}
.nested-columns-a {
 @include grid-column(6);
 background: $box-color;
 height: 200px;
}
.nested-columns-b {
 @include grid-column(6);
}
.nested-wrap {//wrap the small boxes
 @include grid-collapse();
}
.nested-columns-b-one {//small box
 @include grid-column(3 of 6);
 background: $box-color;
 height: 60px;
 margin-bottom: 10px;
}</code></pre>

<hr>
    <h5>Three columns - <span class="secondary">3 into 12 ok</span></h5>
  <div class="grid-four">
  <div class="box"></div>
  <div class="box"></div>
  <div class="box"></div>
  </div>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.grid-four {
 @include grid-container;
}
.box {
 @include grid-column(4);
 background: $box-color;
 height: 60px;
}</code></pre>

<hr>
    <h5>Four columns - <span class="secondary">4 into 12 ok</span></h5>
  <div class="grid-five">
  <div class="box2"></div>
  <div class="box2"></div>
  <div class="box2"></div>
  <div class="box2"></div>
  </div>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.grid-five {
 @include grid-container;
}
.box2 {
 @include grid-column(3);
 background: $box-color;
 height: 60px;
}</code></pre>

<hr>
    <h5>Five columns - <span class="secondary">5 into 12 won't go</span></h5>
    <p>simply use <code>@include grid-column(3 of 15);</code> and it works!</p>
  <div class="grid-six">
  <div class="box3"></div>
  <div class="box3"></div>
  <div class="box3"></div>
  <div class="box3"></div>
  <div class="box3"></div>
  </div>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.grid-six {
 @include grid-container;
}
.box3 {
 @include grid-column(3 of 15);
 background: $box-color;
 height: 60px;
}</code></pre>

<hr>
    <h5>And back to 12 columns and include Shift</h5>
    <p><code>@include grid-column(1 of 12);</code> - <code>@include grid-shift(1);</code></p>
  <div class="grid-seven">
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  <div class="box4"></div>
  </div>
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.grid-seven {
 @include grid-container;
}
.box4 {
 @include grid-column(1 of 12);
 @include grid-shift(1);
 background: $box-color;
 height: 60px;
}</code></pre>

<hr>
    <h5>More Media Breakpoints</h5>
    <p>Set new media breakpoints which changes <code>grid-columns</code> to 4 and 8</p>
  <div class="grid-eight">
  <div class="grid-eight-left">
    <p>At mobile this box is 100% wide
    <br> At 600px this box will span 3 of 4 columns
    <br> At 740px this box will span 4 of 8 columns
    <br> At 900px this box will span 2 of 8 columns</p>
  </div>
  <div class="grid-eight-right">
    <p>At mobile this box is 100% wide
    <br> At 600px this box will span 1 of 4 columns
    <br> At 740px this box will span 4 of 8 columns
    <br> At 900px this box will span 6 of 8 columns</p>
  </div>
</div><!-- grid-box -->
<pre><code class="lang-scss">.grid-eight {
@include grid-container;
p {
 color: $white;
 font-size: $third;
}
}
//see the grid variables at the top of the page
//for grid-media settings
.grid-eight-left {
 @include grid-column(12);
 background: $box-color;
 padding: 10px 20px 0 20px;
 margin-bottom: 15px;
 @include grid-media($small-grid) {//600px
 @include grid-column(3);
}
 @include grid-media($medium-grid) {//740px
 @include grid-column(4);
}
 @include grid-media($large-grid) {//900px
 @include grid-column(2);
}
}

.grid-eight-right {
 @include grid-column(12);
 background: $box-color;
 padding: 10px 20px 0 20px;
 @include grid-media($small-grid) {//600px
 @include grid-column(1);
}
 @include grid-media($medium-grid) {//740px
 @include grid-column(4);
}
 @include grid-media($large-grid) {//900px
 @include grid-column(6);
}
}</code></pre>

<blockquote><p><strong>Note:</strong> Neat is no longer maintained so maybe it's time to look at CSS Flexbox or CSS Grids</p></blockquote>

